She didn't receive and medications there. However, about a week after we brought her home, she became very sick. She had non-rsv bronchiolitis and was hospitalized over night. She was 3 weeks old at this time. She recovered from that, but right away got very sick again with high fever, projectile vomiting, and we went back to the hospital for 3 days. While there she was given a spinal tap, and iv antibiotics as well as Tyelenol and probiotics. The doctors found nothing wrong with her, and we were sent home. She finally did get better, but this was all in the first 2 months of her lifetime.
